# Project Conventions

- Prefer clean, minimal configuration and documentation.
- Use the GitHub repo `dryfolio/info.hovanhoa.net` as the canonical remote.
- Keep README focused on this project (no template-origin references).
- Do not include donation or sponsor badges unless they are explicitly for `dryfolio` or `hovanhoa`.
- When adding new pages or sections, keep the visual style consistent with the existing design (colors, typography, spacing).
- Prefer small, focused React components under `components/` over large monoliths.
- Keep link/bio data in dedicated data/config files (not hardcoded throughout components) so it can be easily updated.
- When copying code from external templates, remove branding/content that is not specific to `info.hovanhoa.net`.